{"cursor":"17238","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":" icon of The Good Thief in Paradise (Moscow School, c. 1560)]]\n\nA 'deathbed conversion' is the adoption of a particular religious faith shortly\nbefore dying. Making a conversion on one's may reflect an immediate change of\nbelief, a desire to formalize longer-term beliefs, or a desire to complete a\nprocess of conversion already underway. Claims of the deathbed conversion of\nfamous or influential figures are commonly used as rhetorical devices, but such\nclaims are rarely verifiable.\n","linknr":212,"url":"Deathbed_conversion","recorded":1362684494,"links":14,"instances":["archbishop","post_1900"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Death","Religious behaviour and experience","Religion and death"],"headings":["Overview","Suggested deathbed conversions","Spurious deathbed conversions","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/Goodthief.jpg/121px-Goodthief.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Raphael_Baptism_Constantine.jpg/220px-Raphael_Baptism_Constantine.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Oscar_Wilde_portrait_by_Napoleon_Sarony_-_albumen.jpg/180px-Oscar_Wilde_portrait_by_Napoleon_Sarony_-_albumen.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["christ's_church_cathedral","hamilton,_ontario"],["luigi_de_magistris","archbishop"],["free_church_of_scotland","post_1900"]],"members":["luigi_de_magistris","free_church_of_scotland"],"related":["Icon","Saint_Dismas","Religious","Faith","Religious_conversion",